Introduction

Security Reference Guides describe the Oracle Fusion Applications security reference implementation. This guide includes descriptions of all the predefined data that is included in the security reference implementation for an offering. The reference implementation can be customized to fit divergent enterprise requirements.


Security Reference Implementation

The Oracle Fusion Applications security approach supports a reference implementation that addresses common business security needs and consists of roles and policies.


Oracle Fusion Applications Security Reference Guides present the following information about the predefined security reference implementation.

  • The abstract and job roles for an offering

  • Duty roles and the role hierarchy for each job role and abstract role

  • Privileges required to perform each duty defined by a duty role

  • Data security policies for each job role, or abstract role

  • Policies that protect personally identifiable information

  • Data security policies on fact and dimension to ensure enforcement across tools and access methods


For an overview and detailed information about the Oracle Fusion Applications security approach, including an explanation of role types, enforcement, and how to implement and administer security for your deployment, see your product security guide.


How to Use this Security Reference Guide

Enterprises address needs specific to their organization by changing or extending the role definitions, role hierarchies, and data security policies of the reference implementation. You may also be subject to specific legal, regulatory, and industry requirements.  You are solely responsible for your adherence to these requirements when assigning roles, privileges and granting access for your enterprise.


For each job or abstract role, review the duties, role hierarchy, and policies that it carries so you understand which users should be provisioned with the role, or which adjustments your enterprise requires before the role can be provisioned. 


Note:

All information presented in this guide can be accessed in the various user interface pages of Oracle Fusion Applications provided for security setup, implementation customizations, and administration. The advantage of reviewing the security reference implementation as it is presented in this guide is that you can more easily compare and plan your customizations.


Tip:

From the entitlement of a role as expressed by privileges, you can deduce the function security enforced by a role. If your enterprise needs certain functions removed from access by certain roles, change the data security policies or duties carried by the role.


Review the data security policies conferred on job roles by their inherited duty roles. 


Review the privacy in effect for a job or abstract role based on its data security policies. Privacy is additionally protected by security components, as described in your product security guide.


Important:

As you make changes to the security reference implementation for an Oracle Fusion Applications deployment, the predefined implementation as delivered remains available. Upgrade and maintenance patches to the security reference implementation preserve your changes to the implementation.



Human Capital Management Offerings


This guide describes the security reference implementation for the following offerings:


  • Coexistence for HCM

  • Compensation Management

  • Workforce Deployment

  • Workforce Development


There is a set of common roles that are required to set up and administer an offering. For information about these common roles, see the Oracle Fusion Applications Common Security Reference Guide.

Abstract Role: Basic Recruiter

Supports integration with Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, identifies workers with responsibilities in Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, but without privileges in HCM. In Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, a Basic Recruiter has limited access to the Recruiting Center and to requisitions, depending on the group membership. Depending on specific needs of each organization, you may duplicate this user type, add, or remove permissions. This default user type provides a good starting point for other recruiting support roles such as assistants and collaborators.

Job Role: Benefits Manager

Manages implementation and administration of benefits business objects and batch processes.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Benefits Manager


Duty Role

Description

Absence Implementation

Manages absence implementation setup using the Oracle Fusion Functional Setup Manager.

Benefits Elections

Manages benefits elections.

Benefits Enrollment Maintenance

Manages administration of employee population using the professional pages and batch processes.

Benefits Process and Report Administration

Manages benefits processes and reports.

Benefits Self Service Setup

Manages benefits self service setup.

Benefits Setup

Manages benefits setup.

Benefits Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Benefits transactional information

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

HCM Extract Definition

Grants access to the extract definition duty.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person Configuration

Manages person types, name formats, checklists, and document types.

Person Management

Manages person related data such as name, address, communications, documentation, and others. This role is associated with the HR specialist.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Transactional Analysis

This duty is used for various generic OTBI security and filtering purposes and is therefore required for all OTBI users

Job Role: Benefits Specialist

Manages administration of an individual employee's benefits using the service center and professional pages.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Benefits Specialist


Duty Role

Description

Absence Implementation

Manages absence implementation setup using the Oracle Fusion Functional Setup Manager.

Benefits Elections

Manages benefits elections.

Benefits Enrollment Maintenance

Manages administration of employee population using the professional pages and batch processes.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person Management

Manages person related data such as name, address, communications, documentation, and others. This role is associated with the HR specialist.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Job Role: Cash Manager

Protects and develops the company's liquid assets maximizing their use and return to the organization.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Cash Manager


Duty Role

Description

Bank Statement and Reconciliation

Reconciles bank statements and transactions. Also manages setup information for bank statement processing and reconciliation.

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Business Intelligence Consumer

A role required to allow reporting from Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office. This role  allow you to run reports from the web catalog but it will not allow a report to be authored from a subject area.

Cash Management Administration

Sets up system parameters, lookups, profile options, and descriptive flexfields.

Cash Management Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Cash Management transactional information

Cash Positioning and Forecasting Management

Manages cash positioning and forecasting

Customer Account Inquiry

View customer account details.

Disbursement Data Management

Manages supplier payments, customer refunds, and employee expense payments.

Disbursement Process Management

Assigns payment process attributes to documents payable, resolves document and payment validation errors, and reviews proposed payments. Views items that were rejected or removed from a payment process request.

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Functional Setups

Uses the functional user overview, and assigned tasks, and task lists.

Import Bank Statement

Allows import of bank statement.

Payments Disbursement Administration

Sets up features allowing disbursement of funds for supplier payments, customer refunds, and employee expense reports.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Subledger Accounting Manager

Creates accounting for transactions, reviews journal entries, and runs account analysis, journal entries, and period close exceptions reports.

Subledger Accounting Reporting

Runs all subledger accounting reports, and reviews journal entries.

Subledger Accounting Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Subledger Accounting transactional information

Transactional Analysis

This duty is used for various generic OTBI security and filtering purposes and is therefore required for all OTBI users

Upload data for Bank Statement Import

Allows to upload data file to import bank statements.

Job Role: Compensation Analyst

Analyzes compensation for a group of workers.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Compensation Analyst


Duty Role

Description

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Compensation Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Compensation transactional information

Transactional Analysis

This duty is used for various generic OTBI security and filtering purposes and is therefore required for all OTBI users


Role Hierarchy

Roles inherited directly and indirectly by the job role Compensation Analyst


Inherited Roles

Compensation Analyst

          Administer Stock

          Business Intelligence Applications Worker

                    Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

          Compensation Transaction Analysis

                    Business Intelligence Authoring

          Download Salaries in Mass

          Manage Workforce Compensation Global Models

          Transactional Business Intelligence Worker

                    Transactional Analysis

          View Workforce Compensation Administration Reports


Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Compensation Analyst


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Administer Stock

Manage stock grants by viewing, updating, importing and exporting stock history.

Download Salaries in Mass

Privilege to download salaries to a spreadsheet, make adjustments to one or more salaries, and then upload changes back into the application.

Manage Workforce Compensation Global Models

Privilege to view and manage global models for workforce compensation plans.

View Workforce Compensation Administration Reports

Privilege to view administration reports for workforce compensation plans.


Privileges

Privileges granted to duties of the job role Compensation Analyst.

Privilege

Compensation Analyst

Analyzes compensation for a group of workers.

Approve Transactions

Manage Market Survey Compensation Type

Manage Market Survey Supplier

Job Role: Compensation Manager

Manages compensation business processes and worker compensation details.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Compensation Manager


Duty Role

Description

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Compensation Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Compensation transactional information

Payroll Batch Load Management

Manages the creation and upload of batches of data.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person Management

Manages person related data such as name, address, communications, documentation, and others. This role is associated with the HR specialist.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Transactional Analysis

This duty is used for various generic OTBI security and filtering purposes and is therefore required for all OTBI users

Workforce Compensation Act as Proxy

Enables compensation professionals to navigate to the Workforce Compensation work area and access worksheets and perform the same actions as worksheet managers. This duty role must not be customized. Doing so will cause undesired results.

Roles inherited directly and indirectly by the job role Compensation Manager

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Compensation Manager


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Administer Stock

Manage stock grants by viewing, updating, importing and exporting stock history.

Administer Workers for Workforce Compensation

Privilege that enables compensation managers to view, enter and override worker level details for workforce compensation plan cycles.

Approve Proposed Progressions and Salary Updates

Review and approve grade, step and salary progressions proposed by the grade step progression batch process.

Download Salaries in Mass

Privilege to download salaries to a spreadsheet, make adjustments to one or more salaries, and then upload changes back into the application.

Manage External Compensation Information

Load and manage data whose source is external to the application which can then be used in a workforce compensation cycle or in a total compensation statement.

Manage Individual Compensation

Privilege to manage individual compensation awards for workers within the user's security profile.

Manage Salaries

Privilege to manage off-cycle salary adjustments as a stand alone transaction or as part of a larger business process such as a promotion or transfer.

Manage Workforce Compensation Global Models

Privilege to view and manage global models for workforce compensation plans.

Review Salary Synchronization Results

Review workers eligible to progress on a grade ladder that requires manual approval before grade, step and salary changes are updated.

Submit a Payroll Process or Report

Submits payroll processes and reports.

View Compensation History

Provides access to view compensation history for workers within the users security profile.

View Portrait Contact Card

Grants access to view the contact card in the portrait, which includes phone number, e-mail, other communication methods, work location information, manager, directs and peers.

View Total Compensation Statements

Views generated total compensation statements for individuals within their security profile.

View Workforce Compensation Administration Reports

Privilege to view administration reports for workforce compensation plans.

Abstract Role: Contingent Worker

Identifies the person as a contingent worker.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the abstract role Contingent Worker


Duty Role

Description

Attachments User

UCM application role for access to attachments using the integrated user interface or the standalone product.

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Business Intelligence Consumer

A role required to allow reporting from Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office. This role  allow you to run reports from the web catalog but it will not allow a report to be authored from a subject area.

CRM Stage Write

Allows uploading CRM content to stage area on content server

Employee Enrollment

Manages employee enrollments.

Expense Entry

Creates and updates expense items and expense reports.

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Item Inquiry

Queries and views items in the enterprise.

Payables Invoice Inquiry

Views Oracle Fusion Payables invoices.

Payee Bank Account Management

Manages supplier bank accounts and other payment details.

Performance Management Worker

Adds content to rate to performance document and evaluates self.

Person Communication Methods Management

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to manage the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person Communication Methods View

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to view the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Portrait Current and Completed Tasks

Grants access to the current and completed tasks card in the portrait, which includes HCM worklist tasks and user provisioning requests.

Procurement Analysis Currency Preference

This role is used to get the supported currencies in Procurement and Spend Analysis module.

Receiving Management Requester

Allows a requester in Oracle Fusion iProcurement to receive items, correct receipts, and return receipts.

Requester Analysis

Duty role with limited access to view and analyze procurement cycle times related to requisitions processing within the Requisition BU that requester belongs to

Requisition Business Unit Data Security

This role is used for Requisition Business Unit data security in the data warehouse

Requisition Self Service User

Manages requisitions including creating, searching, and viewing requisitions, creating noncatalog requests, creating requisitions with one-time locations, and changing deliver-to locations on requisition lines.

Requisition Viewing

View requisition and associated documents.

Social Connection Worker

Performs all Oracle Fusion Social Connection employee duties.

Time and Labor Worker

Reports time as a worker.

Transaction Entry with Budgetary Control

Manages the budgetary control tasks by job roles who perform transactions that are subject to budgetary control, such as accounts payable manager.

View Secured Custom Help

Views custom help containing the security lookup value Secured.

Worker Time Card Entry

Reports time by time card, as a worker.

Workforce Profile Worker

Performs workforce profile duties as an employee or contingent worker.

Abstract Role: Employee

Identifies the person as an employee.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the abstract role Employee


Duty Role

Description

Attachments User

UCM application role for access to attachments using the integrated user interface or the standalone product.

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Business Intelligence Consumer

A role required to allow reporting from Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office. This role  allow you to run reports from the web catalog but it will not allow a report to be authored from a subject area.

CRM Stage Write

Allows uploading CRM content to stage area on content server

Job Role: Employee Help Desk Analyst

An Employee Help Desk Analyst is the first line of user assistance within an IT Department. End users who are having difficulty with any applications they use will register trouble tickets with a help desk. Trouble tickets are routed to analysts who will contact the end user and attempt to troubleshoot and guide the user to successful resolution of their issue.

Job Role: Human Capital Management Application Administrator

Configures the Oracle Fusion Global Human Resources application and has access to all duty roles necessary to implement the Compensation, Workforce Deployment, and Workforce Development offerings.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Capital Management Application Administrator


Duty Role

Description

Absence Implementation

Manages absence implementation setup using the Oracle Fusion Functional Setup Manager.

Application World Reference Administration

Manages application reference industry, territory, time zone, currency, and language, including natural and ISO language.

Attachments User

UCM application role for access to attachments using the integrated user interface or the standalone product.

Benefits Elections

Manages benefits elections.

Benefits Management Implementer

Manages benefits implementation setup using the Oracle Fusion Functional Setup Manager.

Benefits Setup

Manages benefits setup.

Bussiness Process Engineering Human Taskflow Administration

This role grants a user the privilege to perform administrative actions in the workflow functionality via the worklist UI. A user in this role will be able to view all tasks in the system, recover errored (incorrectly assigned) tasks, create approval groups and edit task configuration / rules DT@RT UI (both AMX functionality) This is a business administrator type role. This role is granted to SOAAdmin.

CRM Stage Write

Allows uploading CRM content to stage area on content server

Workforce Structures Management

Manages positions, locations, jobs, grades, and HR organizations. This role does not have any privileges associated directly but inherits privileges from other duty roles. This role is associated with the HR specialist or manager typically.

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Capital Management Application Administrator


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Compare HCM Information

Compares workers, jobs, positions, and any combinations of these objects.

Edit User Name

Updates the user name associated with a person.

Maintain Positions

Updates and deletes positions in the user's position security profile. This role cannot create new positions.

Manage Departments

Manages departments in the user's organization security profile.

Manage Divisions

Manages divisions in the user's organization security profile.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage HCM Rates

Manages derived rates and values defined by criteria.

Manage Payroll Element Entry

Manages the allocation and data entry of earnings and deduction elements to a person.

Manage Person Documentation

Manages documents.

Manage Schedules and Exceptions Assignment

Manages the association of schedules to an assignment. This role is associated with the line manager or HR specialist.

Manage Value Defined by Criteria

Manages values defined by criteria.

Manage Worker Checklist

Manages checklist definitions.

Manage Worker Time Entry Setup Profile

Creates and updates an association of a layout set and time entry actions to control access to any time entries.

Manage Worker Time Processing Profile

Creates and updates an association of rule sets, a time consumer set, and time card periods to report, validate, approve, and transfer time.

Submit a Payroll Flow

Submits new payroll flows.

Submit a Payroll Process or Report

Submits payroll processes and reports.

Use User Details Service

Creates or updates users during person synchronizations.

View Portrait User Account Details Card

Views the User Account Details card in the Person Gallery.

View Positions

Views positions in the user's position security profile.

Job Role: Human Resource Manager

Performs duties of a human resources manager.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Resource Manager


Duty Role

Description

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Contingent Worker Addition

Adds contingent workers.

Employee Hire

Hires employees.

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Goal Management HR Specialist

Goal Management HR Specialist - inherited by Human Resource Specialist

HCM Extract Definition

Grants access to the extract definition duty.

Link User Name to Person

Creates a new user name or links an existing user name for a person.

Manage User Account

Manages user roles.

Manage Users

Creates and updates users and assigns roles to users.

Nonworker Addition

Adds nonworkers.

Payee Bank Account Management

Manages supplier bank accounts and other payment details.

Payroll Common HCM Implementation

Manages all payroll setup definitions required by other HCM products.

Pending Worker Addition and Hire

Adds and hires pending workers.

Performance Management HR Specialist

Manages performance documents to for example, create, cancel, delete, and transfer them.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person Communication Methods Management

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to manage the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person Communication Methods View

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to view the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person Configuration

Manages person types, name formats, checklists, and document types.

Person Management

Manages person related data such as name, address, communications, documentation, and others. This role is associated with the HR specialist.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Portrait Current and Completed Tasks

Grants access to the current and completed tasks card in the portrait, which includes HCM worklist tasks and user provisioning requests.

Succession Plan Management

Manages succession plans.

Workforce Model Plan HR Specialist

Manages workforce model plans, for example, creating, editing, and reviewing the plans.

Workforce Profile Specialist

Performs workforce profile duties as a human resources specialist.

Workforce Structures Management

Manages positions, locations, jobs, grades, and HR organizations. This role does not have any privileges associated directly but inherits privileges from other duty roles. This role is associated with the HR specialist or manager typically.

Description

Ends work terms.

Updates and deletes positions in the user's position security profile. This role cannot create new positions.

Allows the administrator to maintain workers absence records.

Manages derived rates and values defined by criteria.

Manages the allocation and data entry of earnings and deduction elements to a person.

Manages performance goals of workers by HR.

Manages disability information.

Manages documents.

Manages person identifiers for external applications.

Manage Person Image

Manages Person Image

Manages payment methods used to pay a person and defines how the payments are split if multiple payment methods are specified.

Manage Salaries

Privilege to manage off-cycle salary adjustments as a stand alone transaction or as part of a larger business process such as a promotion or transfer.

Manage Schedules and Exceptions Assignment

Manages the association of schedules to an assignment. This role is associated with the line manager or HR specialist.

Job Role: Human Resource Specialist

Performs duties of a human resources specialist.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Resource Specialist


Duty Role

Description

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Contingent Worker Addition

Adds contingent workers.

Employee Hire

Hires employees.

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Goal Management HR Specialist

Goal Management HR Specialist - inherited by Human Resource Specialist

HCM Extract Definition

Grants access to the extract definition duty.

Link User Name to Person

Creates a new user name or links an existing user name for a person.

Manage User Account

Manages user roles.

Manage Users

Creates and updates users and assigns roles to users.

Nonworker Addition

Adds nonworkers.

Payee Bank Account Management

Manages supplier bank accounts and other payment details.

Payroll Common HCM Implementation

Manages all payroll setup definitions required by other HCM products.

Pending Worker Addition and Hire

Adds and hires pending workers.

Performance Management HR Specialist

Manages performance documents to for example, create, cancel, delete, and transfer them.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person Communication Methods Management

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to manage the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person Communication Methods View

Grants access to the employee, contingent worker and Human Resource Specialist to view the phones, emails and other communication methods in the portrait.

Person Configuration

Manages person types, name formats, checklists, and document types.

Person Management

Manages person related data such as name, address, communications, documentation, and others. This role is associated with the HR specialist.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Portrait Current and Completed Tasks

Grants access to the current and completed tasks card in the portrait, which includes HCM worklist tasks and user provisioning requests.

Succession Plan Management

Manages succession plans.

Workforce Model Plan HR Specialist

Manages workforce model plans, for example, creating, editing, and reviewing the plans.

Workforce Profile Specialist

Performs workforce profile duties as a human resources specialist.

Workforce Structures Management

Manages positions, locations, jobs, grades, and HR organizations. This role does not have any privileges associated directly but inherits privileges from other duty roles. This role is associated with the HR specialist or manager typically.

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Resource Specialist


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Access Person Gallery

Searches worker deferred data and views the portrait page.

Accrual Type Absence Plan Balance Adjustment

Allows administrator to enter adjustments for workers in their absence type accrual plans.

Cancel Work Relationship

Cancels work relationships.

Change Worker Location

Changes persons' locations.

Change Worker Manager

Changes persons' managers.

Change Worker Working Hour

Changes the working hours of persons.

Compare HCM Information

Compares workers, jobs, positions, and any combinations of these objects.

Correct Work Relationship Termination

Corrects workers' termination details.

Create Person Assignment

Creates workers' secondary assignments.

Create Succession Plan for Worker

Create succession plans.

Create Work Relationship

Adds work relationships to persons.

Create Work Terms

Creates secondary work terms.

Disburse Accrual Type Absence Plan Balance

Allows administrator to dispense part of an accrual plan balance for payment.

Documentation Reporting

Reports on document information.

Edit Person Career Planning

Allows editing the Person Career Planning.

Edit Person Skills and Qualifications

Allows editing the Person Skills and Qualifications.

Edit User Name

Updates the user name associated with a person.

End Person Assignment

Ends workers' assignments.

End Work Terms

Ends work terms.

Enroll Worker On Accrual Type Absence Plan

Allows administrator to manually enroll worker into an accrual type absence plan.

Maintain Positions

Updates and deletes positions in the user's position security profile. This role cannot create new positions.

Maintain Workers Absence Records

Allows the administrator to maintain workers absence records.

Manage Absence Case

Views employee related absence accrual data.

Manage Accrual Type Absence Plan Enrollment Events

Allows administrator to process Employment Events for workers to determine eligibility and participation in accrual type absence plans.

Manage Contact Person PII

Manages a contact person's PII data.

Manage Departments

Manages departments in the user's organization security profile.

Manage Direct Report

Manages direct reports.

Manage Divisions

Manages divisions in the user's organization security profile.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage HCM Rates

Manages derived rates and values defined by criteria.

Manage Individual Compensation

Privilege to manage individual compensation awards for workers within the user's security profile.

Manage Payroll Element Entry

Manages the allocation and data entry of earnings and deduction elements to a person.

Manage Payroll Relationship

Manages workers' assigned payrolls and other details associated with their payroll relationships.

Manage Performance Goal by HR

Manages performance goals of workers by HR.

Manage Person Disability

Manages disability information.

Manage Person Documentation

Manages documents.

Manage Person Identifiers for External Applications

Manages person identifiers for external applications.

Manage Person Image

Manages Person Image

Manage Personal Payment Method

Manages payment methods used to pay a person and defines how the payments are split if multiple payment methods are specified.

Manage Salaries

Privilege to manage off-cycle salary adjustments as a stand alone transaction or as part of a larger business process such as a promotion or transfer.

Manage Schedules and Exceptions Assignment

Manages the association of schedules to an assignment. This role is associated with the line manager or HR specialist.

Manage Seniority Dates

Allows management of seniority dates.

Manage Succession Plan Candidate

Manages succession plan candidates.

Manage Vacancy

Allows management of vacancies.

Manage Value Defined by Criteria

Manages values defined by criteria.

Manage Work Relationship

Updates work relationships.

Manage Work Terms and Assignment

Manages work terms and assignment records.

Manage Worker Checklist

Manages checklist definitions.

Manage Worker Information Sharing

Shares own employment information with line managers or external parties.

Pending Worker Quick Hire

Quick-hires pending workers.

Portrait Benefits

Views benefits data for a worker in the portrait.

Print Worker Portrait

Grants access to the portrait maintenance duties for the portrait cards.

Promote Worker

Promotes persons.

Report Human Resources Transaction Dashboard

Reports Human Resources Transaction Dashboard

Reverse Work Relationship Termination

Reverses terminations of work relationships.

Submit a Payroll Flow

Submits new payroll flows.

Submit a Payroll Process or Report

Submits payroll processes and reports.

Job Role: Human Resources VP

Performs duties of a human resources VP. This role is associated with compliance and workforce effectiveness analytics.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Human Resources VP


Duty Role

Description

Absence and Leave Accrual Analysis

This duty role is used for analyzing employee historical and future planned absence trends and employee leave accrual balances

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Compensation Analysis

This duty role is used for analyzing employee salary, salary range penetration and the correlation of pay and performance

Employee Data Security

This role is used for Employee dimension data security in the data warehouse

Human Resources Analysis Currency Preference

This role is used get the supported currencies in Human Resources Analysis module.

Legislative Data Group Data Security

This role is used for Legislative Data Group data security in the data warehouse

Payroll Analysis

This duty role is used for analyzing payroll trends including earnings, deductions and taxes; it also allows provides visibility to employee payroll details

Payroll Data Security

This role is used for Payroll data security in the data warehouse

Supervisor Hierarchy Data Security

This role is used for Supervisor Hierarchy data security in the data warehouse

Workforce Deployment Analysis

This duty role is used for analyzing headcount staffing, employee turnover, workforce diversity, internal mobility and employee performance

Workforce Effectiveness Analysis

This duty role is used to view the financial-related workforce benchmark metrics that assess the effectiveness of the organization's workforce

Job Role: Payroll Administrator

Assists with running a company's payroll and responds to employees' questions concerning payroll. They run various payroll processes, print out statement of earnings, reconcile charges, reconcile time sheets, verify payroll items, and verify payroll results.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Payroll Administrator


Duty Role

Description

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Payee Bank Account Management

Manages supplier bank accounts and other payment details.

Payroll Batch Load Management

Manages the creation and upload of batches of data.

Payroll Calculation, Validation, and Balancing Administration

Administers the payroll calculation and validation.

Payroll Completeness Confirmation

Verifies the payroll process results and person process results.

Payroll Distribution Calculation Administration

Administers the payroll distribution of prepayments and costing.

Payroll Implementation View

Views complete payroll setup.

Payroll Payment Distribution Administration

Administers payroll payment distribution.

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Person View

Searches and views person related information.

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Payroll Administrator


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Access Payment Distribution Work Area

Accesses the Payment Distribution work area to manage and track the distribution of payments in payment process flows.

Access Payroll Accounting Distribution Work Area

Accesses the Accounting Distribution work area to manage journal entries for ledgers and costing information related to labor costs, transfer costing results to General Ledger, and define costing setup.

Access Payroll Administration Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Administration work area to manage payroll setup and general payroll administration.

Access Payroll Calculation Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Calculation work area to manage all aspects of calculating and verifying payroll for a group of persons or an individual.

Access Payroll Checklist Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Checklist work area to monitor, track, and update the tasks for each instance of the payroll flows.

Access Payroll Dashboard

Accesses the Payroll Dashboard to view a high level overview of all the payroll business processes and take any appropriate actions.

Access Regulatory and Tax Reporting Work Area

Accesses the Regulatory and Tax Reporting work area to submit and view legislative processes and reports for specific countries or territories..

Adjust Individual Payroll Balance

Manages the adjustment of individual balances.

Manage Costing for a Person

Manages the costing of a person.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage Payroll Calculation Cards

Manages personal information on calculation cards.

Manage Payroll Element Entry

Manages the allocation and data entry of earnings and deduction elements to a person.

Manage Payroll Relationship

Manages workers' assigned payrolls and other details associated with their payroll relationships.

Manage Payroll Third-Party Person Payment Method

  

Manage Personal Payment Method

Manages payment methods used to pay a person and defines how the payments are split if multiple payment methods are specified.

Submit a Payroll Flow

Submits new payroll flows.

Submit a Payroll Process or Report

Submits payroll processes and reports.

View Payroll Report Extract

Secures access to view the payroll report extract data based on the user's legislative data group security profile.

View Payslip

Views payslips.

Job Role: Payroll Manager

Manages all aspects of payroll business processes through setup, data entry, running payroll processes and reports, and verifying and correcting calculated results.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Payroll Manager


Duty Role

Description

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis

Business Intelligence Applications Analysis Generic Duty

Business Intelligence Authoring

An author of Business Intellgence reports as presented in the web catalog. The role allows authoring within Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office.

Business Intelligence Consumer

A role required to allow reporting from Business Intellgence Applications, Business Intelligence Publisher, Real Time Decisions, Enterprise Performance Management and Business Intelligence Office. This role  allow you to run reports from the web catalog but it will not allow a report to be authored from a subject area.

Customer Account Inquiry

View customer account details.

Employee Data Security

This role is used for Employee dimension data security in the data warehouse

FSCM Load Interface Administration

Manages load interface file for import

Functional Setups

Uses the functional user overview, and assigned tasks, and task lists.

HCM Extract Definition

Grants access to the extract definition duty.

Human Resources Analysis Currency Preference

This role is used get the supported currencies in Human Resources Analysis module.

Legal Entities Administration

Manages legal entities, legal reporting units and registrations.

Legislative Data Group Data Security

This role is used for Legislative Data Group data security in the data warehouse

Payee Bank Account Management

Manages supplier bank accounts and other payment details.

Payroll Analysis

This duty role is used for analyzing payroll trends including earnings, deductions and taxes; it also allows provides visibility to employee payroll details

Payroll Batch Load Management

Manages the creation and upload of batches of data.

Payroll Calculation, Validation, and Balancing Administration

Administers the payroll calculation and validation.

Payroll Calculation, Validation, and Balancing Management

Manages the calculation, validation, and balancing of the payroll.

Payroll Common HCM Implementation

Manages all payroll setup definitions required by other HCM products.

Payroll Completeness Confirmation

Verifies the payroll process results and person process results.

Payroll Data Security

This role is used for Payroll data security in the data warehouse

Payroll Distribution Calculation Administration

Administers the payroll distribution of prepayments and costing.

Payroll Distribution Calculation Management

Manages payroll distribution of prepayments and costing.

Payroll Implementation

Manages complete payroll setup and maintenance.

Payroll Implementation View

Views complete payroll setup.

Payroll Interface

Manages the setup and implementation of the payroll interface, allowing the exchange of data between Global Human Resources and third-party payroll providers.

Payroll Payment Distribution Administration

Administers payroll payment distribution.

Payroll Payment Distribution Management

Manages payroll payment distribution.

Payroll Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Payroll transactional information

Person Address View

Grants access to persons to view address data.

Person National Identifier View

Grants access to persons to view national identifier.

Person View

Searches and views person related information.

Subledger Accounting Manager

Creates accounting for transactions, reviews journal entries, and runs account analysis, journal entries, and period close exceptions reports.

Transactional Analysis

This duty is used for various generic OTBI security and filtering purposes and is therefore required for all OTBI users

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Payroll Manager


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Access Payment Distribution Work Area

Accesses the Payment Distribution work area to manage and track the distribution of payments in payment process flows.

Access Payroll Accounting Distribution Work Area

Accesses the Accounting Distribution work area to manage journal entries for ledgers and costing information related to labor costs, transfer costing results to General Ledger, and define costing setup.

Access Payroll Administration Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Administration work area to manage payroll setup and general payroll administration.

Access Payroll Calculation Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Calculation work area to manage all aspects of calculating and verifying payroll for a group of persons or an individual.

Access Payroll Checklist Work Area

Accesses the Payroll Checklist work area to monitor, track, and update the tasks for each instance of the payroll flows.

Access Payroll Dashboard

Accesses the Payroll Dashboard to view a high level overview of all the payroll business processes and take any appropriate actions.

Access Regulatory and Tax Reporting Work Area

Accesses the Regulatory and Tax Reporting work area to submit and view legislative processes and reports for specific countries or territories..

Adjust Individual Payroll Balance

Manages the adjustment of individual balances.

Choose Payroll Report and Process Parameter

Secures access to the parameter values when submitting a payroll process or report.

Manage Costing for a Person

Manages the costing of a person.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage HCM Rates

Manages derived rates and values defined by criteria.

Manage Payroll Calculation Cards

Manages personal information on calculation cards.

Manage Payroll Element Entry

Manages the allocation and data entry of earnings and deduction elements to a person.

Manage Payroll Interface Inbound Records

Manage the payroll interface inbound records from third-party payroll providers.

Manage Payroll Relationship

Manages workers' assigned payrolls and other details associated with their payroll relationships.

Manage Payroll Report Extract

Secures access to manage the payroll report extract data based on the user's legislative data group security profile.

Manage Payroll Third-Party Person Payment Method

  

Manage Personal Payment Method

Manages payment methods used to pay a person and defines how the payments are split if multiple payment methods are specified.

Manage Value Defined by Criteria

Manages values defined by criteria.

Submit a Payroll Flow

Submits new payroll flows.

Submit a Payroll Process or Report

Submits payroll processes and reports.

View Payroll Report Extract

Secures access to view the payroll report extract data based on the user's legislative data group security profile.

View Payslip

Views payslips.

Abstract Role: Power Recruiter

Supports integration with Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, identifies workers with responsibilities in Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, but without privileges in HCM. In Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, a Power Recruiter has permissions on most features and functions within the Recruiting Center, but has limited ability to manage libraries and templates. Depending on specific needs of each organization, you may duplicate this user type, add, or remove permissions. This default user type provides a good starting point for other recruiting management roles.


Privileges

Privileges granted to duties of the abstract role Power Recruiter.


Granted Role

Granted Role Description

Privilege

In Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service, a Power Recruiter has permissions on most features and functions within the Recruiting Center, but has limited ability to manage libraries and templates. Depending on specific needs of each organization, you may duplicate this user type, add, or remove permissions. This default user type provides a good starting point for other recruiting management roles.

Access Oracle Taleo Recruiting Cloud Service

Job Role: Time and Labor Administrator

Manages time and labor system and data, resolves system errors during import of time, validation, approval and transfer processes. Maintains rules, groups, layout sets, and other maintenance tasks.

Aggregate Privilege

Description

Analyze Time Rule Processing Details

Manages setup and maintenance of time rule processing details.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage Worker Time Entry Setup Profile

Creates and updates an association of a layout set and time entry actions to control access to any time entries.

Manage Worker Time Processing Profile

Creates and updates an association of rule sets, a time consumer set, and time card periods to report, validate, approve, and transfer time.

Job Role: Time and Labor Manager

Manages setup, maintenance, and support of Time and Labor. Supervises other roles that support the Time and Labor infrastructure.


Duties

Duties assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Time and Labor Manager


Duty Role

Description

Functional Setups

Uses the functional user overview, and assigned tasks, and task lists.

Time Card Management

Manages time cards that need to be adjusted or submitted for processing, when a worker cannot access their time card.

Time and Labor Transaction Analysis

Analyzes Time and Labor transactional information.

Workforce Scheduling Transaction Analysis

Analyses workforce scheduling transactional information

Aggregate Privileges

Aggregate Privileges assigned directly and indirectly to the job role Time and Labor Manager


Aggregate Privilege

Description

Analyze Time Rule Processing Details

Manages setup and maintenance of time rule processing details.

Generates time cards.

Generates time entries.

Generate Time Event

Generates time events.

Manage Fast Formula

Manages formula definitions used for validation and calculations.

Manage Time Entry

Manages time entries.

Manage Time Event

Manages time events.

Manage Worker Time Entry Setup Profile

Creates and updates an association of a layout set and time entry actions to control access to any time entries.

Manage Worker Time Processing Profile

Creates and updates an association of rule sets, a time consumer set, and time card periods to report, validate, approve, and transfer time.

Unassigned Duties

Human Capital Management offering duties defined but not assigned to any job or abstract role in the reference implementation.


Duty Role

Role Description

Absence Certification Evaluation Scheduling

Schedules the certification process, which assesses certification statuses and due dates.

Absence Entry Through Calendar

Creates an absence record through the calendar.

All Integration Points - All Data

Allows access to all web services and a full access to all data in Oracle Fusion Applications . This role must never be granted to any other role or individual. It is for integration purposes only.

Dutch Person Hiring

Dutch Person Hiring Duty

Employment Action Reason Search

Searches employment actions and action reasons.

Employment Action Reason Selection

Filters the action reason list of values.

Employment Action Type Search

Searches action types.

Employment Action Type Selection

Filters action type list of values.

HCM Integration Administration

Perform administration tasks for HCM related integration activities. Activities include administering HCM Connect integration flows, creating flow components, scheduling flows, and monitoring and administrating the integration flows.

Human Resources Workforce Structures Administration

Administers positions, locations, jobs, grades and HR organizations. This role does not have any privileges associated directly but inherits the privileges from other duty roles. This role is associated with the HR application administrator typically.

Payroll Time Card Validation

Allows access to the payroll time card validation service that verifies the time card data entered prior to batch upload.

Workforce Profile Content Type Data Security Policies

Delivers template data security policies for seeded HCM profile content types. Do not assign to users.
